,Recommended,460920,31512547,Posted: 2 May,all,Ultium,"My Position: Currently have 66 hours in game and have max level and all achievements.Summary: Steep is the first AAA title to return to the Extreme Winter sports game scene after the genre ran dry for several years. Developed by Ubisoft, it has many of the drawbacks and advantages that come with being the firs tto return to the genre as well as being devolped by a majopr company.Buy or no buy? Depends. Here are some pros and cons that I have run into in Steep.+Pros:Unrivaled polish for the genreGraphics are stunnign on maxGreat Environment that can be explored pratcially foreverPartial Multiplayer Experience (more later)Party System (More later)Decent update rate with more maps and gamemodes comingComprehensive Player Customization-Cons:THE PRICETHE OPTIONAL (however surprisingly unobtrusive) MICROTRANSACTIONSOK party system that caps at 4Physics that can seem slidy at timesMultiplayer system that often leaves the game feeling emptyStange Stamina meter physics that makes any good trick feel like complete luckIncomplete Dare system that won't let you even name your own challenges or share them publiclygraphics that run ok at lower settings but scale very poorly. (i.e. Higher settings become harder to run exponetially)Points of Interest are almost to compeltely find without a guide (Could be a plus for some, though I doubt it)2-3 challenges are near impossible to beat (Though many are fixed now)Conclusion: I am a little harsh on this game, mostly out of love, but also because there are problems with the game that I feel make the game forgetable. Part of the appeal of the extreme sports genre is how timeless they can become and how warmly the people who play them look back on them.So do I think players will look back on Steep with warm hearts 5-10 from now? NO. While other titles like SNOW (A free to play on Steam) come nowhere close to Steep in terms of quality, I have no doubt that other large game companies are looking at what Steep here and taking note.Expect to see EA Winter Sports coming soon, as well as other large names entering the field after Steep. Perhaps when gamers go to open their history books, they'll see Steep as the first quirky little seed of a larger green forest.Thanks for reading. :D"
