,Recommended,460920,28184284,"Posted: 4 December, 2016",all,Tibbles,"I've been a huge fan of snowboarding games since the original SSX and have played just about every Tony Hawk's Pro Skater game except the newest one. Overall at bottom.The Main Drawing PointThe main drawing point to this game is being able to switch between sports at any given moment and having random players show up right next to you as you're playing. This game captures that perfectly. It's got that Journey feel to it where the players that you meet can have a huge impact on the gameplay itself.The Missions and CustomizationsThese aspects of the game are well done. Certain clothing are locked behind missions or require steep cash to buy. Steep cash is rewarded for completing these missions as well and how much is determined on if you got bronze, silver or gold. These provide good incentive for players to have a goal in mind, but also to meet and group up with others who are also trying to complete those missions.ControlsThe controls are difficult to grasp and from experience are much more suited to a controller. Keyboard and Mouse are fantastic for FPS games where controllers don’t do so well. Controllers are much more suited for Sports games where keyboard and mouse aren't that great. Doing tricks in this game is one of the main reasons why controllers are just about a must have for Steep. The way you do tricks, put simply, is very much like Skate 3 and fits a controller.Turn off trick safety if you aren't able to do tricks the way you want. It prevents you from doing a trick if you won't be able to land it in time. (Personally prefer it off)OverallOverall I'd give this game an 8.5/10 Fantastic.The game provides a scratch to those who've been itching for a fantastic snow sports game. It's good looking, well optimized and plays well, but way way WAY better if you have a controller. While there are missions, the bulk of fun comes from meeting and grouping up with other players and making the game your own. If you prefer solo play then you just won't get much out of this game. The controls can be difficult at first but with some patience you can master it easily. While the game is everything I've been wanting it obviously isn't going to be friendly for everyone and has some gameplay qwerks that can be off putting to some causing it to receive my score."
