76561198043633862,Recommended,460920,29553747,Posted: 28 January,all,alex_stewart_13,"A beautiful game. Good atmosphere. Definitely has the replay value and is hopefully a good sign of change for Ubisoft. Even if the story is probably the most skippable story I've ever had to play through.I would definitely say that this game is good value for money, which is a rare statement nowerdays especially for myself who has been dissapointed with the gaming industry for the past few years, and Ubisoft has played a big part in my dwindling confidence with the gaming industry.Steep is flawed though, as to be expected by a game from Ubisoft, but these flaws do not apply to every aspect of the game and so do not completely ruin it!The almost gamebreaking camera plagues your every step, making it sometimes impossible to clearly see your path and definitely takes you away from the experience.The way your character interacts with the enviroment is inconsistant and is littered with tweening issues, bugs and glitches. I've discovered that all the issues ive had with the way my character travels around is due to the fact that the game keeps your board flat even if youre on a slope, which means if youre on an uneven surface your character doesnt try to adjust to the changes but simple stays static which leads to the many soul destroying crashes we all have to put up with.The scoring is unfair and is mostly based on luck, last night i just did the same trick for two hours, never getting the same score twice and the scores i did recieve did not reflect what had happened on the screen. Sometimes poorly executed tricks out perform well performed tricks and visa versa. I believe every player has had that moment where they have performed an amazing trick only to be given a +150. Then a while later your character spazzes out on a rock and youre given a score of +3200! In order to play this game you have to suspect disbelief and just wait for the good scores to come.The crashes - Yes...ive messed up. But does my character have to ragdoll down the whole mountain before i can start having fun again? A lot of the time its easier to just retry the event than wait for your character to stop ragdollingStory - ergh.characters - -vomits-Mountain Stories - jesus christ burn them with fire."
76561198085571279,Not Recommended,460920,28814705,"Posted: 29 December, 2016",all,WarPig960,"I REALLY wanted to like this game. I'm not having any issues running it and it looks gorgeous. I can't tell you how excited I was when I heard about Steep. I loved Skate and completed every challenge in the game, and spent hours just free skating and making lines. I'm a bigger fan of snowboarding though and I haven't gotten into a snowboarding game since SSX tricky, which was arcady and completely unrealistic. So I was really looking forward to a more realistic snowboard game, where I could just throw on tunes and go crazy on the mountain. Steep is EXACTLY that, and I was ready to start sinking days into it. I got through the tutorial and started exploring the mountain, found a run I wanted to do and away I went.The controls though... my god... they just don't respond in a way that lets you feel like your character has any sort of flow.The timing just feels very off to put it plainly. You need to jump pretty early in comparison to any other skate/snowboard games, which is awkward at first, but forgivable once you get the hang of it. You use the LS to either flip or spin your character and LT or RT + RS for grabbing and tweaking. The grabbing works fine but the spins and flips seem to only work half the time I want them to. Theres a bit of a sweet spot just as you leave your jump to start a good spin or flip. The landing is where I gave up though. Even if I look like I'm coming into it perfectly, I bail more often than not. The whole experience made me feel more frustrated trying to get my character to do what I want, and land a regular jump FFS, rather than feeling awesome pulling off sweet tricks. Maybe i'm missing something, but it was enough that I uninstalled it. Hope they tweak the controls, it's close to being the perfect snowboard game. But right now I find it more frustrating than fun."
,Recommended,460920,28830324,"Posted: 30 December, 2016",all,introspXtion,"After 10-20 hours of playing, I was going to give Steep a bad review but then everything changed (except for my underwear).The first thing you'll notice is that Steep is visually stunning (like me). It's easy to pick up (also like me) but when it comes to performing like a pro and knowing how best to get the most out of it, it's badly lacking in instructions or tips. Granted this may be because I'm stupid, but it took me longer than usual to figure out why I couldn't land tricks and do other stuff. Also the menu is rather unintuitive and seems to be filled with useless information (like me) that I don't have any interest in.That said, once I figured it all out and had spent enough time exploring the slopes, the enjoyment increased dramatically. By this time I had unlocked more locations and the courses became far more intense and challenging. All of a sudden I was getting nearly more air than what's between my ears and I also began to find locations that I could make a course/challenge out of. The speed you get on the steepest slopes is exhilarating and the slightest mistake will have you crashing like my mum on a motorbike. The wingsuit had also gone from getting into a starfish position and falling, to zooming through tricky rock canyons and caves that are destined to give you more brain injuries than what I’ve accumulated in real life from riding on the back of my mum’s motorbike.Paragliding has still yet to excite me but it is useful for exploring, especially as it can climb up when you get some wind under you and I kinda like the exploration element of the game. The narration during parts of the game tries to be cool but is pretty dull (like me once again) but totally makes up for it in the fashion stakes by offering numerous jackets in pink, though I would’ve liked to have seen 1-piece lycra bodysuits like they wear at the Winter Olympics. I like lycra.I could name a number of bugs, issues and things that should've been in the game but for $40au (on sale) I’m more than happy with my purchase.★★★★★★★★★✰"
