,Recommended,460920,34441765,Posted: 23 August,all,Limes,"Just a summary:+ Graphics, it's a gorgeous game.+ Sound effects are good and add a lot of atmosphere.+ Mountains are good, huge both of them with almost infinite possibilities for great trails. A lot to explore even after many hours into the game.+ Several sports to choose from, wingsuit is a highlight for me. The extreme pack adds 3 more but the new ones are kinda situational and there aren't many challenges for them yet.+ Challenges are well designed for the most part, some of them are kinda hilarious.+ Community challenges add replayability since they're constantly adding them.+ Customization is alright. Several characters to play and a lot of costumes, clothes and gear skins.+ Replays and director mode are great, you can make very very nice videos of your rides.+- Leaderboards are good to have and being able to spectate the best times and such is nice but they are too small and should allow for easier browsing and let you choose any trail from the top 10 at least, etc.+- Trick system. While there's more depth to it than it appears at first I find it a bit clunky sometimes and the G-system can get in the way and become bothersome forcing you to slow down too much or fall. IMHO there should be a freeride mode that does away with this or tone it down a lot, but I get that they're going for more of a sim game than arcade.+- Multiplayer stuff could be better but what's there is ok. I haven't played much with people but trying to beat friend's scores was fun.+- Stories. Although most of them were fun to complete, some had terrible voice acting and were very cheesy or silly in a bad way.- No character progression beyond cosmetics and no stats even for the gear. Apparently every snowboard is identical.- Music isn't very good and the way it's implemented annoyed me a lot. The constant slow down on fall clashes with the way the challenges are designed (hard ones are repeat after repeat until you get it right). After a while I completely turned it off and began playing my own things while in the game. They should allow players to play custom music anyway like other games do. Pretty meh feature.- Mountain navigation is pretty terrible and imprecise, clunky UI. I ended exploring as much as possible and then just playing the challenges from the start menu instead most of the time. Also, you can't input coordinates manually and sometimes you do need to go to a specific location, very bothersome having to move the pointer around until you more or less find the area.Tl;dr: A good game not without its flaws. Don't expect SSX at all. Probably worth playing for the wingsuit gameplay alone :)."
