,Recommended,460920,30763212,Posted: 26 March,all,GoldPlease,"I see a lot of people talking about Steep in a really binary way. There are the people who think Steep is trying to be a snowboarding/skiing simulator and argue that it's a realistic game. There are also the people who argue the opposite -- that Steep is trying to be an arcadey game  like the old Tony Hawk games or SSX.To me Steep is neither of those things, Steep is a game that is meant to simulate the *feeling* of skiing and snowboarding. When I'm at the top of some random mountain crest and I pick a line, power through it, and throw in a few nice looking tricks where and when it feels right, I truely get the same feeling I get from actual snowboarding (a mix of adventure and creativity). Likewise when I'm doing some challenge or replaying a race over and over to get that perfect run -- I feel like I'm playing a video game. The beauty of Steep is its ability to toe the line between a fun game and a simulation of something I really enjoy. That is why Steep will be staying downloaded and In my library for a very long time."
