,Not Recommended,460920,29015981,Posted: 4 January,all,JollyClaret,"I refunded this game. Let us begin why.Firstly Steep could be used to describe the pricing of this game. It's worth noting I bought the game for £26.79 during the Steam Sale, yet I still think valuewise this is a £25 base price game.You may say ""How can you review the game with just 2 hours played?"" Well I assume this is the reason Steam made the refund time 2 hours to give the ability for the consumer to sample it enough to see whether it is enjoyable. After two hours Steep made the refund list.Don't get me wrong, Steep is enjoyable but it isn't a game you will play for a long time and you probably won't be playing it in a years time. Why? The game is repetitive. Yes this game goes for a more realistic approach similar to Skate does for skateboarding but the difference is I can still try interesting tricks in Skate that might be impossible in real life, Steep doesn't offer that luxury. The wingsuit is fun at first but ultimately tedious. The paragliding is just the worst it's boring and sure it is nice to look at the great graphics, it eventually loses the dazzling nature.What this game is really missing is fluidity. I can switch from my wingsuit to paragliding of course, but then I must land, be on foot and then switch to my snowboard. Where is the ability to attach your snowboard midair and as soon as you land go straight into snowboarding?Microtranscations, it's Ubisoft. Should be nuff said but for the unintiated Ubisoft are massive cockwombles when it comes to microtranscations. Noted it's not so bad here but basically everything ingame can be bought for real world money. Why do you need to further monetise a game which costs full AAA price and and has a season pass? This is a greedy business practice.Character customisation, very poor. Sure the ability to tweak accessories is very cool, but can I actually customise the physical aspects of my character? No I have to choose from presets. I have no clue why this is the case.I'll probably get flack from the hardcore fans of this game but Steep isn't worth £39.99, a lot of the postive reviews have even said so. If you absolutely must have this game, pick it up next time it is on sale for £26.79. It's not a bad game by any stretch, it's very beautiful, and I am sure extreme sports fans will enjoy it, but it leaves much to be desired. It's not as good as it could have been."
