76561197989949090,Recommended,460920,30709427,Posted: 24 March,all,[PAK]ADHD,"I'm a huge snowboard fan, and at first glance, Steep has all it takes for an excellent game.Casually exploring endless gorgeous slopes while pulling off sick stunts is sublime joy of this game.Which gets interrupted as soon as the game tries to force you into narrow-scoped parts of gameplay. Which alone are not that bad if not for:-Speed and three star courses challenge controls which are not set for precision - which leads to endless attemts to beat these courses. In fact, you cannot enjoy this game fully without a decent gamepad.-Lack of well-designed progression. Yes, you have level and earn currency for outfits. But it doesn't change what you do and how you do it. It's too sandboxy and doesn't engage for lenghts. The career should be more peculiar and directional, with championships to qualify, sponsorships to chase and things to spend dough on.-Fast-travel becomes too common. New slopes get unlocked instead of being discovered - you loose track of surroundings.-In-game store lacks of major brands.-No social activities. Yeah, you can bump into couple of people here and there but there's nothing to do together to stay in touch. Ideally, you would chat with people about cool slopes while in the chairlift - to then get there and explore.-Annoying region lock. Why should Ubisoft deprive customers of choice of language? Not to say that it came with the chinese pack when installed.-Offputting price. Regardless of your region, the game costs premium. On top of that, there's microtransactions.Oh, and remember how much you paid yesterday? IT'S ON 50% SALE A DAY LATER.-Other sports are kinda... meh.Note it's just a perfectionist criticism.I rate the game 7.7/10, and will come back over and over. Just maybe not that often."
