76561198043671592,Recommended,460920,29973008,Posted: 16 February,all,tifferoni,"Steep is one of those games where you probably will need to have experienced similar games prior to playing it to enjoy it [Think Amped or SSX] however, unlike those more traditional sorts of snowsports games, Steep takes it one step further and makes it open world. You can do whatever you want, you aren't bound to any obligations, but you do have to do challenges to level up. It's challenging, seeing other players randomly is also very nice too, it makes it feel a bit like Journey in the sense that you don't see 100 people around you at once, but you'll get a few in there to give you more of an 'I'm not alone on this mountain journey' vibe.Really the only negative thing I can think of is once you run out of money to earn through the story and challenges there is no way to make money anymore so there will not be any 'unlock every piece of gear' runs, which is unfortunate. Hopefully that has been fixed or updated by the time you read this review."
,Recommended,460920,29424009,Posted: 22 January,all,JapanGamer29,"I'm really enjoying Steep. The controls are easy to pick up, and it's fun playing through the numerous challenges trying to better your time or score. If you visit mountain tops or some of the easier challenges, you can find other people to join and either race against or explore with. Personally, as a real-life mountain person, I love just freeriding off the beaten path until I reach the edge of the map. It's an experience you don't often find in a video game.Snowboarding and skiing are great, and wingsuiting is exciting, but a bit more difficult. Paragliding is slow and boring, though sometimes the best way to travel from peak to peak. I haven't bought the DLC yet, but would like to have the sled option, too.As for performance, I've had no problems worth mentioning. The game looks great and runs smoothly on my machine (i7-4770K, GTX770, Windows 10).If you're a sports fan or outdoor lover, then Steep is a must have. Others might enjoy the novelty for a few hours, but that's probably it."
