,Recommended,460920,28208138,"Posted: 5 December, 2016",all,Zoanox,"I'll start this review by saying that the game is rather over-priced, it doesn't really have much of a purpose to it other than complete some challenges, it feels like doing the sub-quests in an Assassins Creed game. Aside from that, the game plays rather well, smooth fps and great graphics, a few minor details that could look more realistic, but for what it is right now it's very nice.The gameplay is very fun if you're interested in those addrenaline filled sports but don't have the money or the balls to actually go out and do it yourself in the real world. This game would be excellent if it was played in VR (virtual reality).One personal issue I've ran into is the game crashed numerous times, however I found out that was due to my Graphics Card overheating and going into ""Nope-Mode"" to save itself from any cheeky damages. I have never ran into such an issue with the card on any other games, most of which are newly realeased / high-end games. Keep an eye on your hardware temps with this one, just in case. To remedy this I moved one of my many case fans to get better air-flow to the GPU, you can also try leaving your case door off / open. This may also have been due to hot weather however it still didn't happen with other games that day. Just a heads up for anyone else on a possible issue!Anyway, I would give this game a solid 7 / 10 - loses points for being a bit over-priced and having that ♥♥♥♥ing stupid GoPro Karma drone in it, ♥♥♥♥ing worst drone ever released.. And loses points for some bad hardware compatibility. Gains points for a decently well made game despite the GPU temperature thing, sound effects are fine, graphics look great, and the gameplay has a nice feel to it."
