,Not Recommended,460920,28211986,"Posted: 5 December, 2016",all,GooberDanger,"As an avid snowsports enthusiast I honestley wanted to like this game. You can choose to belive me, or write me off as some kid who has never been in snow a day in his life. I've been skiing for 9 years, and started snowboarding 2 years ago. I spend every weekend at our local resorts, and go after work during the week sometimes. Thats where I noticed the first issue on this game. The controls are very rigid feeling, movements simply don't transfer as expected and you notice the little bugs fairly  quickly. Theres no chance to catch your edges on either skiis or the snowboard and all you can do are basic grabs, spins and flips, which the mechanics for are absurd. There is almost no variation for park terrain and there are no boxes / rails present anywhere in the game. Gliding through pine trees poses no tree well risk, theres not really any hidden rocks or drops either. I wanted to love this game, but after 2 hours it just feels so stale already. The challenges are all ""go here and ride this"" ""go here and do 12 seperate backflips"" It's just not worth $60.Tl:dr I've been on mountains for years, the realisim in this game is completley missing, the missions get incredibly stale and it's just not worth $60 for a ""full game"". If there was more terrain, and a grinding system, more control over your ride ect. I would come back. But for now, it's time for the steam refund process."
