,Not Recommended,460920,28925730,Posted: 1 January,all,God Himself,"To get straight to the point, this game is not worth the $40 on sale, much less the $60 it costs when not unless you absolutely know that this is the type of game you could never get bored of.Now, about 20 minutes of my almost two hour playtime was trying to get it to actually work, because I had to uninstall the game three times before it would stop crashing on start-up, so there's that. Once I got into the game is what pretty fun for a while, but I stopped in fear that I would exceed the two hour limit mark of essentially, ""free"" play time because I wasn't sure if I actually would play this game enough to put the $40 I spent to justice.Eventually the next day I came back and played for about 60 minutes, but thankfully stopped just in time before the 2 hour mark at 117 minutes.The thing is, the game is so linear that it's basically just five ways to go down the mountain till you get close enough to drop points and challenges to spawn at so you can then do those challenges to increase your rep to unlock spawn points higher up on the mountain so you can repeat the entire process.So like, here's a really bad analogy of the progression of Steep.Say Steep is like a layered fruitcake.The top of the cake is the top of the mountain, the bottom of the cake is the (you guessed it) bottom of the mountain.You start at the relatively bottom of the mountain with fruit surrounding you. The fruit represents challenges.Now, you start off doing the challenges around you, which gains you reputation.When you recieve enough reputation from challenges, you get to progress to the N E X T L A Y E R O F F R U I T C A K E .You start at the top of that new layer, and are tasked with making your way down the layer in any means you're given.Thus, the process repeats itself till you're at the top of the mountain.Pretty linear, if you ask me, since the challenges are basically split into two categories among all of the four sports.Skiiing and snowboarding which are on the ground has challenges split into two groups and they are either:-Ski/snowboard down the mountain as fast as you can.or-Ski/snowboard down the mountain at your own pace but you have to do tricks to get points.Wingsuiting and Paragliding are the other two sports which are a bit different.Wingsuiting challenges are either:-Wingsuit down the mountain as fast as you can, while going through the checkpoints.or-Wingsuit down the mountain while staying as close to the ground or other objects as possible.Paragliding goes like this:-Paraglide as fast as you can through some checkpoints.or-Paraglide at your own pace while doing some flips and♥♥♥♥♥♥Now these are pretty linear, making the game seem pretty repetitive after a while so unless you REALLY like the concept, you'll be wasting $40."
