,Not Recommended,460920,30506522,Posted: 14 March,all,Freebie,"what can I say? Its practically Shaun Whites surf boating with updated textures and levels. Besides the awkward jump button and laggy input response its a pretty okay game. The reasons I would not recommend this game include the sad G Force mechanic, the input lag, the overall buggy terrain, the slight luck factor and its lame music.The G Force mechanic is your biggest enemy in this game. It adds an unnecessary realism to the game that sometimes gets too real when you are going for the quad front off a cliff side with 4 seconds hang time. The best part is when you are carving at a reasonable speed and hit a hidden lip causing you to catch slight air, do a 90 degree spin resulting in a topped out meter.Lets talk about the input lag. This mainly concerns the jump button. When approaching the lip of a jump you may hit another one of those tiny hidden jumps which causes your preloaded jump to cancel out. This leaves you riding of the main lip without any hang time and can really grind you gears. This occurs quite often. Another input lag issue regards flips and spins. I believe a month into the games release they apparently fixed flips and spins. On its first month of release you flipped or spun by flicking the stick right after you released jump. Once you figured that out things got fairly consistent. After the update they changed the flip and spin controls so that you could flick yo stick almost any time around jump release. The problem now is that its somehow less consistent as it was before. Now when you go for that quad frontflip off a big ole cliff you may end doing a single flip at an extremely slow rate. Very steezy looking, but not really good for racking up points.The terrain is A+ in this game. Gorgeous and realistic as all hell. The main issue with it is that it can get rather buggy sometimes. It mostly has to do with structural terrain. You will be mobbin at a jump, preload jump button, hit the bottom of transistion and all of a sudden half your speed disapears, you release jump and do 1.5 flips and land right on your face. If you have ever hit steep transistion in real life wether on a skateboard, bike or skiboard, you know you have to do a little hop  while transistioning in order to retain most of your speed. Unfortunately the game nor you (with jump) can accomplish this resulting in a lousy jump. When flying down a mountain it can sometimes be hard to spot small relief. If you are turning at high speed and manage to catch air off of it you will spin and you will goof up your clean g force meter if you manage to ride it out. Its like in real life. Almost as real as doing a quad fronty off a large cliff side.The luck factor is strong with this game. Expect to retry some challanges hundreds of times. This is mainly due to reasons listed above. Your multiplier is not easy to earn and will go away with any wipeout. wiping out due to reasons listed above  is common even with your taller than dad ""vidya game skill level"".The music is pretty lame. Feels like you are in a modern Disney movie. Where is DIO? Why no Jay zed? No Bhi Bhiman? They have included an option to turn off copyright music. This option is gauranteed to play some tunes you have never heard before but the selection seems microscopic.If you purchase this game and manage to hit Play, expect to become a slave to it. My ""Y"" button on my wired Xbox controller has been squished thousands of times from constantly retrying challenges.Thanks for reading. Add me if you want to master debate about this game."
