76561198007252580,Recommended,460920,29439018,Posted: 23 January,all,Sordel,"When Steep was announced, most of the influencers I listen to dismissed it immediately as a rather substandard & unexciting proposition. Still, I was keen to give it a go, having sunk countless hours into SSX Tricky and Amped 3, and while it's not as good as either of those it scratches the same itch.On the plus side, reloading a challenge is instantaneous on my system and so is quick travel; this is technically impressive and keeps play sessions brisk & fun. The mountains are vast, giving a real sense of unlocking a massive playground. Moreover, the sports themselves are fun, with paragliding & wingsuiting adding much-needed variety to the basic ski/snowboard option. The result kept me playing for hours on end and it's definitely the sort of the game you could fire up just for a relaxing cross-country ski.The negatives? Well, the game engine has barely improved from early console snowboarding games with irritating collision detection, a clumsy trick system and dumb ragdoll physics: sure, it's fun, but we should have moved on to something more robust by now. The quick reloads come at the cost of some ugly draw-in & pop-up. Some of the challenges are frustrating. And - maybe it's a small thing - but there doesn't seem to be a water engine in this game at all: no running streams or waterfalls to add to the Alpine atmosphere.Overall, though, this is already a good package that could be improved further with DLC. One to add to your library when it's discounted."
