,Recommended,460920,29367636,Posted: 19 January,all,Jacket,"TL;DR: I give this game an 8/10, because, as it is a lot of fun and full of content, there are a few problems with it.I've given myself pretty ample time to mess around with Steep. If you like the nostalgia of games like SSX or the Amped series, mixed in with the heavy, realistic-focused feel of the Skate series, this is a highly recommended title.In 9 hours of playtime, I feel like I've only scratched the surface of the gameplay even though I've been playing challenges and mountain stories non-stop. The mechanics are smooth, doing tricks is fun, the scenery and snow deformation are beautiful, and the microtransactions, while present, are pointless because of how easy it is to get in-game currency through challenges to buy cosmetics (which is all the currency is for).I only have a few gripes, which are the following:-Pressing the button to try a challenge again will sometimes put you back in the same place but about a foot backward, causing you to go down the OTHER side of a hill if it's angled on the backside.-While I have pretty great internet, the always-on DRM is worrying just because it's there. There is also no way to turn off multiplayer, and as such, performance hits can sometimes occur when encountering players because it has to track their playermodel among an already taxing scenery engine.-The G-Force system, while providing a more realistic experience, can sometimes be a nuisance; even if you land a trick at the exact angle of the mountain facing the perfect angle, you can lose a substantial chunk of health even off a small jump. Overall, I think that mechanic needs some tweaking.-The only things to do are free-roam around and do challenges. They are plentiful and there are tens of hours of content to be enjoyed, however, I would have liked to see a career mode or something similar with even a light storyline or something else to do that gave the game a more complete feel."
