ce. So bad.Some quality of life improvements needed, but other than that its a pretty fun game when stupid things don't happen.  Wouldn't drop 60 bucks on it though, get it on sale."
76561198126162656,Recommended,460920,30209460,Posted: 26 February,all,Fennec,"Personially I highly enjoy and recomend this game. Its a beautiful and well crafted experance that takes in the wonder of the Swiss Alps, or recently Alaska. It also allows for diffrent players and playstyles to thrive in the same environment, with 3 diffrent modes of transportation: ski/snowbord, wingsuit, and paragliding. If that's all you need to hear, then click ""Buy"". However, this is deffenitly not a geme for everyone. Here's why:The controlls are purposfully somewhat loose. You might hear people relate this game to SSX, and rightfully so, but you wont be able to do SSX things. In order to jump, you dont just press a button, but release it. To prime a jump you need to hold down the right or left trigger of your controller, and then release it slightly before you wish to jump. For someone who participates in skiing/snowbording this quickly became second nature, but for those who dont, it might take some getting used to. Tricks are some what complicated as well. Directly after initiating a jump, NOT AT THE SAME TIME press a direction on the left joystick to initate rotation, and release to stop rotation. Your rider will right himself durring a jump, but you need to give him time to do so. In order to land well, and not waste g-force meter, you will need to release the direction almost a full second before you reach the ground. When in the air, you can use the left or right trigger to grab with the left or right hand of your rider, and use the left thumbstick to tweak your trick in the air. This all seems very complex, and for some, the inputs to do a simple trick, might be too complexSteep can be repetitive, some chalenges can start to feel the same after a while, and it can be confusing how the maps and chalengs work, as well as finding them in the maps. After all chalenges are complete, you can retry them for a higher score, or just roam the map and find your own lines. The late-game gameplay is very explorative and open ended, and can be offputting for some.Everything is not for everyone. I say that I highly recomend this game and that I love the way it controlls. At the time of writing this review, I have almost 40 hours in the game, and I would guess that about 30 min of that is spent paragliding. Some people might really enjoy paragliding, but it's not for me, and I would say as a general rule, to not go in expecting to love everything about this insainly varried game. it trys to do allot well, and might not hit perfect notes on everything. but what you do find and enjoy, is what makes this game really amazing.With the FREE Alaska dlc, I would recomend steep more than ever now. But buyer be warned, if you like your games to always be fresh every time, and are not one for reppitition, steep might not be for you. If you dont mind that, however, i think you'll really enjoy this game."
