76561198090471022,Recommended,460920,31164392,Posted: 15 April,all,M0nk3y_Ceratops,"I had my eye on this game for a very long time before I bought it, and when i finally rounded up the money, i bought it straight away, and lemme tell ya -worth every penny spent- after only 4-5 days i had around 10 hours in the game. The limitless exploration, the thrilling challenges, the nerd gasm worthy graphics, the fluent movement, perfect atmosphere and absolutely amazing sound track makes this game possibly one of the best games i have ever played. Which says a lot from me, a hack n slash kinda player.I'll go through each of the things i listed above, just to convince you to get this game even more:1. ExplorationThe game gives you plenty chance to explore, and the game even constantly urges you to do so with the dialogue of the game (which is actually pretty darn good too). I've gone on several runs alone, just to see what i havent seen (which there is still a lot). There's just so much to see, whilst also feeling like a total badass as you shred jump after jump.2. ChallengesThe game's medium and hard difficulty runs are actually crazy difficult and pull you in to complete the challenge very well. Ive spent up to 20 minutes sometimes just to get that gold medal, and its such a relieving feeling.3. GraphicsThe graphics make the game breath taking almost every moment. That's all you need to know.4. AnimationsThe animations are so fluent and realistic sometimes you almost feel as if you're inside of the game, especially when looking at replay in first person and listening to the freakishly realistic audio from your gopro. The way the snow carves with every movement is so satisfying. The life in the character you play is real and nearly perfect. Your clothing moves in the wind, just thought you might need to know that, cus i find it awesome.5. AtmosphereYour surroundings make it always feel as if you're the best skiier/boarder tackling the hardest slopes.6. Music/SoundsThe music can either make you feel like the coolest guy on the mountain, or quite relaxed and feeling you're just there for a good time, without putting out your attention or bringing boredom, which few relaxed games can do. The ambient sounds feel so natural and great, as with the crumpling or sliced snow beneath you as you carve down the mountain or take a trek up the mountain to reach the best spots.In conclusion, buy the bloody game!"
