,Recommended,460920,28262806,"Posted: 8 December, 2016",all,Poop Tickler,"Previously I wouldn't have recommended this game but that's no longer the case.This game is great.The scenery is what is stressed by the developers and it does not disappoint. I have found myself sitting on the side of the mountain for brief moments of time looking at the world around me. There is a calming sense of enjoyment with Steep. It's easy to simply sign in and pick up where you left off. The soundtrack is great and offers some customization (filter certain genres of music). Personally I like to ride down a mountain at full speed listening to what relaxing music this game offers me. There isn't an obvious story, nothing for cut scenes. You'll find your own challenges that yield currency and cosmetic awards. All the equipment handles the same, and while you do level up certain styles of playing (free style, extreme riding, pro riding) they grant little more than experience. When you hit the level cap you are able to teleport anywhere you like instead of using challenges and landmarks to get you there. Lets more effectively break down what went right and wrong.The graphics are fluid and show much detail. It is GPU heavy, I run ultra settings w/ my GTX 970, 80 FPS. They have various environmental alterations that you can choose from, night riding, heavy fog, evening, morning etc. This also means that your friends with you will not see the exact same ambiance. Steep offers an easy to use replay mode to record your sessions, take screen shots, and change the ambiance in game for those of you looking for specific shots.The mechanics and physics are on the right track but ultimately become a problem at times. Steep uses a ""magnetic"" system that will pull your player in any direction in the air. This means that sometimes they will rotate to the side, slamming into a rock or hill. It becomes inconvenient at times. For the most part, it works but you WILL see it happen your first hour into the game. Ubisoft has released 3 updates and none of them have addressed this issue.Finally, the dev involvement is there! They have hopes to push the game into certain directions. There is a free DLC to be released next month with a few new mountains to explore.Definitely worth picking up for those looking for a relaxing game that you can kill time on."
76561198053701090,Recommended,460920,29407800,Posted: 21 January,all,Infamous,"Steep is an open world Ski/Extreme Sports game with a lot of potential.I really love this game!The map is huge allowing you to explore for hours, a variety of different challenges and no serious competetive elements at all. The soundtrack to the game is great and the sound design is top notch. The graphics are beautiful and surpise me with how well they run on my computer and with (most of the time) steady frames. Customisation is lacking though, don't get me wrong there is quite a variety of what you can customise but in each section there isn't too much to customise, e.g there are quite a lot of helmets but barely any variety in gloves. The game is a bit buggy and if i'm honest, sometimes you lose momentum for no reason and i've managed to glitch through a few walls. However, for what it's priced at (40 pounds in the UK) I don't feel the game is worth it, I personally waited until the game went on sale and got it for about 26. Although this idea isn't fresh in the industry, Steep does differ from other similair games like SSX with it's atmosphere and vibes the game gives you, I feel really mellowed out when playing which I don't really get from many games. To be clear, I haven't played with friends yet but I HAVE played with randoms and trying to get the high score on certain challenges is really fun without having to take it seriously. In my opinion though, one of the things that let this game down is that it really feels like something is missing. Although you can Walk/Snowboard/Ski and Fly, it doesn't feel like it's enough, I think snowmobiles would be a cool feature further down the line as the game is still kind of in its early days, but for now I'm happy to keep things like this. My final thing that I would like to nag about is the fact that some challenges in particular are boring as ♥♥♥♥, for instance one of them consisted of literally following an AI whilst some voice over went on about its fetish for the mountains (sounds funny but at the time I would rather have fallen down the slopes and cracked my neck).The biggest complaint I see from OTHER people is that the game gets repetetive and boring, so if you're extremely in-patient then I suppose this isn't for you. I can understand the idea of using the same mechanics over and over again can get boring after a while, but really what do you expect from a sports game? It's like buying handball 2017 and then saying ""this is boring, how come I can't kick the ♥♥♥♥ing ball?""TL;DRI recommend this game (WHEN IT'S ON SALE)Pros:-Great graphics-Huge map-Something fresh-Music fits well-Online-A decent amount of customisation-Basically what it says on the tinCons:-Buggy at times-A few challenges are pointless-Frames can stutter MASSIVELY now and then-Tutorial is a bit long and I don't think it's skippableRating: 8.5/10"
,Not Recommended,460920,28763510,"Posted: 28 December, 2016",all,steeleybaws,"Personally I'm rather neutral on this gameProsVery Beautiful:This game graphically is absolutely stunning. Personally I use a GTX1060 at max settings 1080p and I'll be getting a nice 80fps. The snow textures and everything else make it a truly fascinating game to look at.Open World:So glad that this is the kind of game where you can do whatever the hell you wanna; playing with friends and making your own lines makes it feel like an aspect of freedom.Ride Replays:The ability to replay rides in my opinion makes this game great, gives so many opportunities to take screenshots for wallpapers (got a lovely one myself), and also for making neat edits.Soundtrack:A lot of the music in here is very atmospheric which fits the game so perfectly, also includes those great classic bangers to be boarding down a mountain to.Customisation:Loving how many different wing-suits, snowboards, skis, and helmets there are to provide a great ability to make your rider look however you want them to. The only reason I haven't included the other items of clothing (Goggles, gloves, jackets, trousers, boots, and parachutes) is i feel that there aren't enough that look half decent, many may disagree with me on this but I think most of the jackets/trousers are boring and same with the boots. Goggles are pretty much all the same too just different colours. Hoping that Ubisoft will continue to add to this game to bring in some more good looking gear.ConsG-force ""Health"" Bar:Personally I'm not a fan of this in some aspects, it particularly needs fixing with the rocks.. Even just sitting still on a rock your rider will experience enough G to knock him/herself out. I don't know if this is on purpose or just something accidental. Hoping it is sorted out soon.Price:I think that trying to charge £40 for this game is a step too far from Ubisoft. I understand that this is the usual price for a high end brand new game but for a game that isn't very filled £40 is just a bit too much. Plus trying to get another £16 for the season pass is just too steep (but being me I bought it).Skiing:Is it just me or does the rider (when using skis) insist on landing backwards? No matter how hard I try the automatic system to smooth out your landing always seems to point me the other way, nothing wrong with it it's just a bit annoying to be honest. Skiing poles: The rider loves to wave his/her poles around but not actually use them for their intended purpose, to help you move.. Was hoping that the rider would use their poles to help them speed up on sections where they have lost speed and need to gain, however this is rarely the case.Saves:Personally I have found that 2 challenges fail to save no matter how many times I do them (these being ""All Scores"" and ""Snowpark""). I'm not sure if this may just be a problem with me.Neutral PointsAutomatic Landing:Was quite pleased to see that the game will complete the trick for you and land relatively smoothly. This is a great feature as i find that it helps people who may not be used to this style of game and makes it that bit easier. However... Often the system will make the rider land sideways (when completing a cork or such like), causing him/her to either fall off or enduce a high gforce and thus restricting them from tricks for a while.Even though I do enjoy this game very much and continue to play a few hours every day; I would not recommend it due to its high number of flaws (price, mechanics, etc). But if you don't mind spending this much on a ""not quite as good as it should be"" title, go for it"
