76561198338201813,Recommended,460920,28782740,"Posted: 29 December, 2016",all,BellisJ01,"So I'm not going to give it a thumbs down, but I will say that despite how much I wanted to enjoy this game, it just wasn't for me.First off, yes, I have less than an hour of gameplay, not nearly enough time put in to give any sort of review. So I will say that I would still recommend this game, as I do like the concept, but I just felt that me personally wouldn't be putting much time into it.So for the Pros;~   Beautiful scenery and well optimized. Very rarely would I have any kind of fps drop.~   As a long time snowboarding fan, I like how it feels like, well, snowboarding. It has a slight arcade feeling, but for the most part it doesn't feel over the top.~   Squirrel suit is pretty fun. Fast and can be a bit tricky, but still fun.~   I like the idea of an open world, desipte me not putting the time in to actually explore, the freedom of being able to  choose where you want to go, or start is pretty cool.Cons; (Just me personally)~   I didn't really care for the controls too much, and yes, I was using and xbox one controller. It just feels a bit odd and clunky.~   Over saturation of tutorials. I am the kind of person, whether it be a movie or a game, if I'm not sucked in pretty quick I'll lose interest. So spending the first 20 or so minutes of the game going through the motions of the different sports, locations, line challenges, etc... was a bit of a turn off. I like to be placed in a world and have to just figure the game out. Much like Dark Souls I guess you could say.~   Always online: While this isn't a huge problem for me personally I could see how it could be for others. I spend a lot of time away from home in hotels, so trying to do any online gaming on unstable hotel wifi isn't the most fun thing in the world.So overall I would give it a 5/10. Which is a shame because I really wanted to love this game. While the lack of arcade is what was appealing to me, maybe that's what this game needs more of. So if you're a wintersports fan, I still recommend this game. But if you're anything like me, and some of these cons outweighted the pros, then I would suggest holding off until a price drop, or maybe some tweaks and/or content patches."
