,Recommended,460920,29104166,Posted: 7 January,all,Technomancer,"Brief summary: the concept for this game is great. It plays out pretty well and enjoyable overall, but there are MAJOR problems that turn an otherwise great game into a very average, blood pressure raising s***show. The controls are pretty easy to pick up and doing tricks is fairly simple. The game has a very large map and once it is loaded from the menu, you will not have any loading screens while you move about to different peaks.[This part has the negative aspects] HOWEVER, there are some absolutely gamebreaking problems with this game. First of all, the physics engine is completely broken AND the game is unforgiving.  It would be one thing to have a bad physics system with forgiving gameplay, but Ubisoft says F%%% you, we don't care. The physics engine has no idea what friction is nor how gravity works. If your board TOUCHES anything other than snow, you are dead. The rocks will either have infinite friction, act like magnets and suck you into them, or launch you at infinite speed. This is a major problem in some challenges (BOBSLED CHALLENGE) because the physics make it impossible to even complete. In addition to this, jumping is cruel. You have to jump well before you leave the ramps, so many of the smaller jumps are practically impossible to time properly. You end up with a .05 second window to execute a jump or you fail.NEUTRAL PIECES. The characters are either forgettable or obnoxious. They try to make a story or something out of the game, but nothing is coherent and you just cram challenges in so you get gear, XP, and credits. It would be cool (and really easy) if they made this something like a ""career mode"" and you created a character and progressed through challenges (kind of like Tony Hawk's Underground back in the day). You just get to Mont Blanc as quickly as possible and forget about any dialogue or any sort of narrative the game tries to feed you.Overall, it is hard to recommend this game. If you can find it on sale, buy it. I paid $40 but still feel bad about the price. If you can get it for $30 or less, then buy it. The concept is excellent and the game is great fun when it is working properly. HOWEVER, when the game is NOT working properly (physics engine, I am looking at you), then it makes you want to punt puppies across the room.tl;dr the game has its moments, but it is so broken in other aspects that it only makes it a 6.5 out of 10. Some challenges are great fun and others make your blood boil.Fix the physics engine and it will easily be a solid 8.5/10. This game is AWESOME when it is working correctly."
