,Recommended,460920,31419597,Posted: 28 April,all,LordFarquaad,"This is one of those games that i HIGHLY recommend. It is really just that awesome. I love winter sports and even my buddy that doesnt love winter sports loves this game too. I love how much time and effort Ubisoft has put into developing this game and there a still many more updates to go.This game has awesome mechanics and great features both online and when playing alone.The controls are so simple on both keyboard and controller, personally i prefer the keyboard but i pretty sure most prefer the controller. It doesnt work so well with the steam controller, a little fiddling is needed to get a comfortable layout, but Xbox 360 controllers work wonderfully.I love the madness in the game, you can see a screen shot of my rider with a deer hat on in the middle of the night and the air on my profile page.Downsides include the season pass :D Although i did happily purchase this, its anoying that it even exists. However i do think the stuff they've promised for that purchase is deffinately worth it.Another downside for me is that i cant put my own music playlists in which isnt so bad because their tracks are pretty decent. The music can just get slightly tedious.These are relatively small complaints and thats impressive considering the size and comlexity of SteepHope I help you make a decision!Deffinately a highly recommended game."
,Recommended,460920,28769295,"Posted: 28 December, 2016",all,BruckFL,"I can understand some mixed reviews for this game. Overall the graphics and scenery are stunning, the soundtrack/audio is excellent ( I love the crackling in the fresh powder), and about 99% of the time I enjoy the game as a whole. I do feel there are some issues, the controls can be annoying (especially when trying to do a speedrun and you want to level your character out but then randomly flips or turns more than wanted) and the similarity of challenges can lead to boredom. I feel those who have a skiing or snowboarding background will get the most out of this game. I love being able kick back and start a run while listening to the chill music to relax, but I do feel there can be simple additions that make this game so much better and realistic such as being able to ride snow lifts to a drop, being able to ride down to resorts or cabins as in real life and walk around, more of a real life story interacting with other characters would add so much to this game, but overall this game is solid"
