76561198047734421,Not Recommended,460920,30914920,Posted: 2 April,all,FranklintheTMNT,"(Serious) Edit: yea, this game has gotten somehow worse. If you don't set your audio in windows to the lowest quality, the sounds in this game has a lot of static. Game no longer auto-detects steam controllers. Changed review to DO NOT RECOMMENDSteep is a superhero game where you are a youtube content creator in a post-apocolyptic arctic wasteland. In this world, you have an adamantium skeleton adapted to withstand an infinite amount of force. You are able to withstand a force that would otherwise kill a normal human being, and shake it off as if you tripped and caught yourself. However, this power comes at a great cost. Your adamantium skeleton is not equipped with the independent capability of jumping without augmentations such as 2 or 1 flat feet, or augmented wings. The problem still persists in your web-suit form.The world has changed very much since the present day. Every single non-youtube creator has uploaded their consciousness to the cloud. As a result, you have to have a constant internet connection to continously upload your extreme videos of you reverse-trustfalling the ground in a wingsuit or you will automatically DC and die. Also, entire villages were abandoned and no human lives in the ""real world"" anymore, only the corporate sponsors. This gets so riled up, like I just drank a Red Bull® and am consumed with the primal energy to strap on my GoPro® and go shred some snow in my North Face®Due to the high demand of computing power thanks to uploading of the entire human conciousness, you must acquire the best computer parts. I have made the mistake of playing this game without upgrading my 16 GB of RAM to 32 GB or closing google chrome; I lost the game after 5 minutes and the game quit automatically to save me the embarrasment.But shredding the mountain man. It's hella on fleek af fam or whatever kids are saying these days. So shred and whatnot.TL;DR unoptimized, sponsored, lack of basic controls, but actually a fun game. Wait for a sale."
